-- Nova Scotia Liberal Party Returns to Power With Election Win
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2013-10-09T01:21:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-09/nova-scotia-liberal-party-returns-to-power-with-election-win-1-.html
The Nova Scotia Liberal Party will
return to power for the first time in more than a decade after
winning a majority of seats in provincial elections today.  The Liberals, led by Stephen McNeil, were elected or
leading in 33 of 51 electoral districts, according to results
posted on Elections Nova Scotiaâ€™s website as of 10:10 p.m. local
time. The Progressive Conservatives were ahead in 11 seats and
the governing New Democratic Party led in seven seats.  Premier Darrell Dexter led the NDP to power for the first
time in the last campaign in 2009, and held 31 seats in the
legislature when the election was called last month. The
Liberals had 12 seats, the Progressive Conservatives held seven,
with two vacancies.  The Liberals have been out of power in Nova Scotia since
losing elections in 1999.  To contact the reporter on this story:
